The State-of-the-Nation-Address (Sona) by President Jacob Zuma to be held in Parliament next week, will leave motorists and pedestrians with temporary road closures, parliament said on Friday. Due to the Sona ceremony on Thursday, the road closures in and around parliament will take effect from Tuesday, with full road closures on Thursday, the document from parliament document said. The parking restrictions and road closures will commence at different times on different streets over the next upcoming days. African News Agency For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.